sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1472614
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All the desaturase sequences are derived from the Synechocystis sp. but optimised for the expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This protein generator is composed of the delta 9, delta 12 and delta 15 desaturase genes with an RBS upstream of each coding sequence and LacI regulated promoter. Desaturases introduce cis-carbon double bonds to the carbon chain of fatty acids. ∆9 desaturase introduces a double bond to stearic acid between carbon 9 and carbon 10 to produce oleic acid. ∆12 desaturase introduces a double bond between carbon 12 and carbon 13 of oleic acid so to produce linoleic acid. In the end, ∆15 desaturase converts linoleic acid into alpha-linolenic acid by adding a double bond between carbon 15 and carbon 16 (Figure 1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The desaturase genes in plasmids were introduced into E. coli for amplification. The final construct includes iGEM provided RBS (BBa_B0034).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lau Tsz Kit

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1027001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Delta 9 Desaturase, optimised for expression in Escherichia coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesized gene based off the protein sequence from Synechocystis sp
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This enzyme is obtained fro the gene Stearoly Co-A Desaturase (SCD). The gene is obtained from Synechocystis sp., a cyanobacterium.It is involved in the biosynthesize of C18:1 from C18:0. C18:1 corresponds to Oleic acid. The delta 9 desaturase introduces cis carbon double bond on the 9th carbon in C18:0.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimized for expression in E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Harrison, Lorna Hepworth, Vun Hiang Tan

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1027002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Delta 12 Desaturase, optimised for expression in Escherichia coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Produced synthetically based on protein sequence from Synechocystis sp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This enzyme is obtained from the gene Oleic acid desaturase (ode).The gene is obtained from Synechocystis sp., a cyanobacterium and introduced in the E.coli. It is a trans-membrane enzyme, involved in the biosynthesis of C18:2 from C18:1. C18:2 corresponds to Linolenic acid. The delta 12 desaturase introduces a second cis carbon double bond on the 12th carbon in C18:1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimization for expression in E coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Harrison, Lorna Hepworth, Vun Hiang Tan

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1472610
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The amino acid sequence of delta 15 desaturase is derived from Synechocystis sp. but codon optimised for the expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence encoded for the delta15 desaturase. The gene is from Synechocystis sp. and optimised for the expression in E. coli. During the fatty acid conversion process, delta 15 desaturase catalyses the conversion of linolenic acid (18:2) into alpha-Linolenic acid, ALA (18:3) by adding a cis-doube bond at carbon 15.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The enzyme cut site must be designed according to iGEM prefix and suffix requirements.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Choi hiu Ying, LEE Cheuk Lam, Tse Yui Shing, Yeung Sin Yu
